header.gameNote: FRANKLIN AMERICAN MORTGAGE MUSIC CITY BOWL

videos.description: Benny Snell Jr. dives in from 3 yards out to give the Wildcats an early lead against Northwestern in the Music City Bowl.
videos.headline: Snell pounds it in as Kentucky strikes 1st

videos.description: Jeremy Larkin finds Clayton Thorson on a throwback pass and Thorson goes down with an injury at the end of the play.
videos.headline: Northwestern QB Thorson injured after reception on trick play

videos.description: A group of Wildcats defenders come over to shake hands with Northwestern QB Clayton Thorson after he suffered a leg injury.
videos.headline: Kentucky players show great sign of sportsmanship

videos.description: Justin Jackson runs it in for a 5-yard score on their first play after the Wildcats lost their starting quarterback.
videos.headline: Jackson puts Northwestern on top

videos.description: Kentucky's starting running back, Benny Snell Jr., pushes the official's hands away after a tough run and gets ejected from the game.
videos.headline: Kentucky's Snell ejected for making contact with ref

videos.description: Northwestern's Stephen Johnson dives to make the interception off of the tipped pass.
videos.headline: Johnson makes great diving pick

videos.description: Justin Jackson dives over the pile to extend Northwestern's lead.
videos.headline: Jackson leaps in for another TD

videos.description: Head coach Pat Fitzgerald believes his backup quarterback Matt Alviti will perform in the second half.
videos.headline: Fitzgerald says it's next man up for Northwestern

videos.description: Northwestern's Clayton Thorson goes down with an injury, but Kentucky players approach him on the sideline and wish him the best.

tracking.trackingName: NCF One-Play (Thorson gets injured on trick play, Kentucky shows respect) 2017/12/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Thorson gets injured on trick play, Kentucky shows respect

videos.description: Kentucky's Stephen Johnson runs in for a 3-yard touchdown to get the Wildcats back in the game.
videos.headline: Johnson gets in on the QB keeper

videos.description: Jeremy Larkin zooms in to the second level to set up Northwestern in the red zone.
videos.headline: Larkin rips off a 64-yard run

videos.description: Kyle Queiro shows off his ballerina feet on the sideline and runs in for the 26-yard interception return for a touchdown.
videos.headline: Northwestern's Queiro tiptoes the sideline for pick-6

videos.description: Stephen Johnson runs it in from 9-yards out to put Kentucky down 1 late, but the Wildcats fail on the 2-point conversion.
videos.headline: Kentucky goes for two and the win, but falls short

videos.description: Coach Pat Fitzgerald's Northwestern Wildcats won their 10th game despite losing their starting quarterback in the first half.
videos.headline: Fitzgerald proud of his team getting to 10 wins

videos.description: Kentucky fails on a game-winning 2-point conversion in the final minute and Northwestern wins the Music City Bowl 24-23.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Kentucky falls short to Northwestern in Music City Bowl) 2017/12/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Kentucky falls short to Northwestern in Music City Bowl
